## 5. Accessibility (WCAG 2.2)

Financial applications have legal accessibility requirements. All of these are non-negotiable.

| Rule                  | Requirement                                                        |
|-----------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Contrast (text)       | Minimum **4.5:1** ratio for normal text                           |
| Contrast (UI)         | Minimum **3:1** for icons, borders, graphical components          |
| Touch targets         | Minimum **24×24px** for all interactive elements                  |
| No color-only signals | Profit/Loss must include **↑↓ icons AND text**, not just color    |
| Form labels           | Every input must have a **visible label** — no placeholder-only   |
| Focus indicators      | Visible keyboard focus ring on all interactive elements           |

### Signal Cards Accessibility Example
```tsx
// Correct — direction communicated via color + icon + text
<span className="text-profit">↑ Bullish</span>

// Wrong — color only, no icon or text
<span className="text-profit">●</span>
```

---

## 6. Component Defaults

- **Default theme**: Dark mode
- **Charts**: Smooth area/line curves with gradient fills under the curve
- **Stat changes**: Show percentage delta with colored arrow (↑ green / ↓ red)
- **Tables**: Monospaced font for all numeric columns, alternating row backgrounds `#1E1E1E` / `#242424`
- **Sidebar**: Icon-based, compact, left-aligned; active item uses `#635BFF` accent
- **Cards**: `#1E1E1E` background, `12px` radius, `1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08)` border
- **Badges**: Pill shape, semantic background at 15% opacity with matching text color
